to see the environment variables:

printenv are case sensitive

printenv HOME

env variables are upper case

echo $HOME


creating an env variables

export VAR="value"

eg:

export EDITOR="vi"

export TZ="US/Pacific"

Remove Envi Variable:

unset VAR

Eg
unset TZ

Persisting Envi

$ cat ~/.bash_profile
export TZ="US/Central"




